{"word":"ἁψίς","slug":"ἁψίς","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ἁψίς</b></el> <br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:ἅπτω'><el>ἅπτω</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li750'><b>1. </b><i>a juncture, loop, mesh</i>, such as form a net, <b><a href='S:Iliad'>Il.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><i>the felloe</i> or <i>felly</i> of a wheel, <i>the wheel</i> itself, <b><a href='S:Hesiod'>Hes.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>3. </b>any <i>circle</i> or <i>disk</i>, of the sun, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>4. </b><i>an arch</i> or <i>vault</i>, <b><a href='S:Plato'>Plat.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Lucian'>Luc.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}